NVIDIA's CFO said recently in a conference call that inventory levels for gaming GPUs were at a historic low level due to cryptocurrency miners. "We do think that cryptocurrency has been a very significant factor in both revenue and pricing, creating a shortage environment that is boosting pricing," Morgan Stanley analyst Joseph Moore said..
